track_notes: Climbed ridge up to Carlintooth Rig, going became tussocky until I reached the shooters track but not too bad ground for walking on. It looked interesting going down so I walked down the ridge to the west of my ascent, tussocky again but there is an interesting little sweetspot where the two burns merge into one at the bottom of Grain Head. Then you just pass the sheepfold to rejoin the track. The shooting track has now been extended right over Roan fell so an activation could be done on a bike as others have done in the past but not by using my route. If you go on two wheels use the track all the way.
track_title: Roan Fell from Farm road at Twislehope
